DIGEST
SB 1 Engrossed 2026 Regular Session Jenkins
Present law relative to the Open Meetings Law, provides for the recordation of votes made
by members of public body in the minutes, journal, or other official, written proceedings of
the body and shall be a public document.
Proposed law provides that a vote displayed by an electronic machine shall satisfy viva voce
voting and the Open Meetings Law.
Proposed law provides for the retroactive application of this Act.
Effective August 1, 2026.
(Amends R.S. 42:14(C))
